        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Calculated value. The European production volume is extrapolated from the Global production volume, which is approximated with the annual Global production capacity, using the average GDP (constant 2017 international USD from 2015-2019). The annual Global production capacity of polyether polyols was 9.4E9 kg in 2016, according to the producers capacity. Here, half the polyol production capacity was assumed to represent the short chain production.This value is multiplied with the European share of global GDP, 19.6% (mean of 2015-2019).


References:
https://www.statista.com/statistics/747099/production-capacity-of-the-leading-polyether-polyol-producers/, accessed 11-09-2023.
World bank (2022): GDP, available here:  https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/NY.GDP.MKTP.PP.KD, accessed 17-05-2022.

</productionVolumeComment>
